txt.en:
'Do you see the creature ahead? He is a terrible Gorthorog, among the strongest they have in their force here. I have seen that one defeat at least a dozen Rangers.

'We call him the Titan of Tyl Annûn, he never steps foot off this island. He stands there and makes us fear coming here.

'It is time to put his reign of terror to an end. Let us defeat the beast.'
'The abomination has fallen and Tyl Annûn is a little safer. There are still many more to deal with, but now I tread here with more confidence.'
A terrible Gorthorog stands on the terrace of Tyl Annûn, overlooking the whole of Lake Evendim.
Defeated the Titan of Tyl Annûn
Defeat the Titan of Tyl Annûn
The Titan of Tyl Annûn must fall.
Orchalwë will want to speak of the battle with the Titan of Tyl Annûn.
